00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:43.440
and how they influence
our spiritual well-being?

00:02:43.440 --> 00:02:44.160
Sure.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:45.840
Let's get started right away.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:48.240
It's a slightly complex topic.

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:52.720
We'll try to understand this
as best as we can.

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:56.000
At the very outset, I would 
like to once again say

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:01.840
that whatever we discuss
in response to your questions,

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:06.880
a lot of that knowledge comes from
the teachings of Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi,

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:11.360
the founder
of Sahaja Yoga meditation,

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:14.160
and intertwined, of course,

00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:17.920
with what we know about
human anatomy and physiology.

00:03:17.920 --> 00:03:19.680
So let's get started.

00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:25.040
Before we try to understand how the autonomic
nervous system and the subtle system

00:03:25.040 --> 00:03:28.720
sort of are correlated or interact,
let's take a step back

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:33.520
and see what constitutes 
the subtle system.

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:38.720
And from there we can proceed towards
our understanding of the autonomic nervous system.

00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:44.000
The so-called human subtle system,
as you'll see in the animation,

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:49.840
comprises nadis.

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:58.160
Nadis are — it's a Sanskrit word —
and it can have multiple meanings.

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:04.160
It can mean nerves, it can mean channels,
it can mean tubes, it can mean blood vessels,

00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:08.400
it can mean lymphatics,
it can mean a whole host of things.

00:04:08.400 --> 00:04:12.720
It's almost like one word,
or like a noun for a collective,

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:18.160
for a whole host of individual things
within the body.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:22.720
This system was described in detail

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:29.040
by the Yoga Sutras of Patanjali.

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:34.880
This is a very ancient Sanskrit text,
and what you have in those texts

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:39.600
is a description 
of this subtle anatomy

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:42.640
or physiology
within the human body,

00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:45.040
within the human system.

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:50.240
What the subtle system is actually,
if we step even one step further

00:04:50.240 --> 00:04:51.920
or kind of step behind,

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:56.960
is actually a reflection
within us of the macrocosm.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:58.400
So, what do we mean?

00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:00.880
What we have within us is the microcosm.

00:05:00.880 --> 00:05:04.560
What exists outside of us,
is the macrocosm.

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:10.160
And within the macrocosm, if we look
at how things function,

00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:15.680
there is a system of balance:
light and dark, heavy and light,

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:20.400
dry and wet, fire and ice.

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:26.080
So, those are naturally occurring phenomena
that are present in nature.

00:05:26.080 --> 00:05:31.520
It has also been described—let's say, what
we spiritually or metaphorically refer to

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:32.960
as yin and yang.

00:05:32.960 --> 00:05:37.520
Just as there is daylight, there is night;
there is the sun, there is the moon;

00:05:37.520 --> 00:05:40.240
you have high tide, you have low tide,
so on and so forth.

00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:43.680
You have summer and spring;
you have fall and winter.

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:54.560
So, in nature we have a balance,
and systems which, if overactive,

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:56.480
can trigger an imbalance.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:06:00.640
In other words, if we have too much heat,
that isn't good for the system;

00:06:00.640 --> 00:06:06.080
if it's too cold,
it isn't good for the system in general.

00:06:06.080 --> 00:06:11.920
So, ecology, or ecosystems
or the universal constants that we see around us

00:06:11.920 --> 00:06:16.560
is a very good way to begin
to get an understanding

00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:20.400
of what the human subtle system is about.

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:23.280
To slowly start coming

00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:28.160
into the details and trying
to answer the question.

00:06:28.160 --> 00:06:31.840
As the human being evolved,
or as the Homo sapiens evolved

00:06:31.840 --> 00:06:36.720
as we discussed the last time,
the nervous system was an adaptation

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:41.120
to evolutionary pressures,
and those evolutionary pressures

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:48.240
engendered two broad
systems of phenomenon

00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:50.000
from a Darwinian point of view.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:54.240
The first one was
the fight or the flight response.

00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:57.120
The fight or flight response
comes into play

00:06:58.240 --> 00:07:01.680
if there is a threat to the
organism in the environment,

00:07:01.680 --> 00:07:06.800
and then it leads to what Darwin called
natural selection,

00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:12.320
or it brings down pressure upon the system
or upon the species to take

00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:20.240
or to adapt such characteristics
that allows it to thrive in the environment.

00:07:20.240 --> 00:07:23.040
So either it can overcome the danger,

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:25.840
a smaller fish
could be gobbled

00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:32.320
by a bigger fish, so maybe it needs to develop
more sensory organs, faster fins, faster reflexes.

00:07:32.320 --> 00:07:36.320
Similarly, a gazelle on the Serengeti plains
needs to develop responses

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:39.760
to run away from the lion
that might pursue it.

00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:42.320
So, those are flight or flight responses

00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:46.720
that are part of
the evolutionary mechanism.

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:52.320
So, the subtle system
comprises two aspects to it.

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:59.600
One is a passive aspect, and
the other is an active aspect.

00:07:59.600 --> 00:08:04.480
So, we see that even in the cosmos around us,
things are dynamic,

00:08:04.480 --> 00:08:06.880
and sometimes they are passive,

00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:10.160
both at the same time, and
it's not a contradiction.

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:17.920
The whole system through immutable laws,
and we call them the laws of divinity,

00:08:17.920 --> 00:08:24.000
the laws of the Almighty,
call it what you will, to each his own,

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:29.520
but the system works
in a state of balance.

00:08:29.520 --> 00:08:35.280
So, likewise, in the human body,
now to start coming back to the point,

00:08:35.280 --> 00:08:38.800
we have a system
which is the passive system;

00:08:38.800 --> 00:08:41.280
we have a system which 
is the active system.

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:43.440
On the left side, so to speak,

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:48.160
we call it the moon channel,
or we call it the Ida Nadi;

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:53.840
on the right side, we call it the sun channel,
or we call it the Pingala Nadi.

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:58.000
The left side, or the moon channel, 
is more passive; it allows passivity,

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:01.920
but passivity that doesn't mean
sloth or lethargy.

00:09:01.920 --> 00:09:04.400
It can get into it if it is overactive.

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:09.280
Similarly, on the right side,
we have the ability to act,

00:09:09.280 --> 00:09:14.320
to bring our desires into fruition,
but again, if that becomes overactive,

00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:15.840
that becomes a problem too.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:20.480
We can become: aggressive, overthinking,
overplanning, that sort of a thing.

00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:27.200
So, within the human body, the subtle system
has these two components; they are called Nadis,

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:29.600
and that's how it functions.

00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:34.000
Now, back to, once again,
to the evolutionary component.

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:38.240
Within the evolutionary system, as we said,
there is a flight or fight pressures,

00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:41.760
but there is also the need to evolve.

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:47.360
The need to evolve into a higher state,
both at a physical,

00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:53.600
but as well as at a cognitive,
or at a nervous system level,
or at a neural level.

00:09:53.600 --> 00:09:57.040
And that is how we described
during the last session

00:09:57.040 --> 00:10:01.520
how the brain evolved
in response to some of these pressures.

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:05.680
So, likewise, in the subtle system,
there is a third component,

00:10:05.680 --> 00:10:10.800
the so-called Sushumna Nadi,
and that is a kind of power

00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:14.640
that allows evolution to proceed.

00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:20.080
We know how these changes are brought about
through genetic changes that are passed

00:10:20.080 --> 00:10:26.080
onto the offspring from the parent
that has allowed it to survive.

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:31.040
These are the three components
of the subtle system.

00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:34.960
On the left side, the passive side,
the so-called Ida Nadi;

00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:39.920
on the right side, the so-called sun channel,
the active side or the Pingala Nadi;

00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:42.960
and in the center, we have a power

00:10:42.960 --> 00:10:48.240
that allows evolution but,
evolution in a spiritual sense.

00:10:48.240 --> 00:10:56.400
The microcosm is reflected in the macrocosm,
and now we come to the autonomic nervous system.

00:10:56.400 --> 00:11:00.320
The autonomic nervous system
also has its two components.

00:11:00.320 --> 00:11:06.160
One is the sympathetic nervous system;
the other is the parasympathetic nervous system.

00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:11.360
The sympathetic nervous system
governs your flight or fight responses.

00:11:11.360 --> 00:11:14.400
For example, a human being sees a danger,

00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:17.840
either he or she wants to fight

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:19.280
or to run away from it.

00:11:19.280 --> 00:11:24.000
That triggers your heart rate
to either pump faster,
maybe run away from the danger.

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:25.680
So that's one.

00:11:25.680 --> 00:11:30.560
The other is the evolutionary,
or the parasympathetic nervous system.

00:11:30.560 --> 00:11:36.160
The parasympathetic nervous system
is your rest-and-digest system.

00:11:36.160 --> 00:11:42.080
It allows the individual to repose,
to relax, and to nourish.

00:11:42.080 --> 00:11:46.640
The left and the right,
the subtle systems,

00:11:46.640 --> 00:11:51.840
or the sympathetic systems,
are something that are energy-expending systems.

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:54.320
They consume energy; they expend energy.

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:58.720
We either consume energy in our desires,
by having desires,

00:11:58.720 --> 00:12:02.800
or we consume energy
bringing those desires into action.

00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:08.560
The parasympathetic nervous system allows us
to rest and to nourish ourselves,

00:12:08.560 --> 00:12:14.240
and in that way, through mechanisms
that we have not yet biologically elucidated,

00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:16.080
allow us to evolve.

00:12:16.080 --> 00:12:16.880
I'll stop there.

00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:21.040
I hope that that kind of answers the question,
but I'm happy to take more questions

00:12:21.040 --> 00:12:24.560
if that did not fully explain it.

00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:29.440
Thanks, Dr. Ashish, for that explanation.
And as we continue to zoom

00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:33.280
into the subtle system,
after having understood a bit about

00:12:33.280 --> 00:12:38.080
these energy channels or these Nadis,
we would like to understand from you

00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:40.240
a little bit about the plexus now.

00:12:40.240 --> 00:12:42.960
So, how is a plexus formed?

00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:47.040
What role do plexuses play
in the functioning of the human body?

00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:51.040
Things of that nature,
if you can explain to the audiences.

00:12:51.040 --> 00:12:51.760
Sure.

00:12:51.760 --> 00:12:58.000
So, a plexus is derived
from the Latin word,

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:02.720
and it means a braid,

00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:07.840
like a braid of hair, for example,
like women who have hair, longer hair,

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:14.640
or even men or women, if you tie that in a braid,
that's the word, that's the origin of it.

00:13:14.640 --> 00:13:15.360
That's how it looks.

00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:18.320
Why is it called a plexus?

00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:22.960
We saw last time that the central nervous system
consists of the brain and the spinal cord,

00:13:22.960 --> 00:13:28.480
and through the spinal cord
which passes through the vertebral column,

00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:32.400
you have nerves that come out
of the vertebra from the sides.

00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:38.720
When the nerves come out from the vertebra,
they come together

00:13:38.720 --> 00:13:46.480
from different parts, and the plexus is like,
if you open the electrical box

00:13:46.480 --> 00:13:50.640
in your house, you see a bunch of wires
coming together.

00:13:50.640 --> 00:13:55.680
So, a plexus is like nature's way
of organizing the nerves.

00:13:55.680 --> 00:14:01.040
The nerves that come out,
and these nerves, as we know, go further out,

00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:04.000
and they enter the various organs of the body.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:06.160
So, whether it is the heart,
whether it is the lungs,

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:10.160
whether it is the stomach,
the pancreas, the liver.

00:14:10.160 --> 00:14:13.600
And also, of course,
the skeletal musculature.

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:17.840
So, these nerves, when they come out,
they bunch together,

00:14:17.840 --> 00:14:22.320
they come together,
and that is what is called a plexus.

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:30.000
A plexus is,
from a Sahaj point of view,

00:14:31.520 --> 00:14:40.720
the gross manifestation of what we call
energy centers or chakras within the body.

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:46.560
The Yoga Sutras have described
seven principal energy centers.

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:51.120
There are multiple other centers as well,
but there are seven energy centers

00:14:51.680 --> 00:14:55.600
that start from something
that is below our vertebral column,

00:14:55.600 --> 00:14:59.520
right up the way,
right into the crown of our head.

00:14:59.520 --> 00:15:08.800
The hypothesis is
that the energy center itself exists

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:13.200
at a very, very subtle level
within the human body.

00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:18.400
The energy center, or the chakra,
cannot actually be seen

00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:22.960
through any current means
of diagnostic techniques,

00:15:22.960 --> 00:15:27.680
for example, MRI scans
or functional MRI scans or CT scans.

00:15:27.680 --> 00:15:32.400
You cannot put something in
and try to see it functionally,

00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:35.520
nor can you dissect the body at a level
where you see it,

00:15:35.520 --> 00:15:42.720
because these energy centers function
or exist at the plane of energy.

00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:46.000
It is not a matter per se; it is energy.

00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:50.880
And these energy centers, at specific parts
of the human body,

00:15:50.880 --> 00:15:56.800
govern the functioning
of these nerve centers we call plexuses.

00:15:56.800 --> 00:16:03.680
The energy flow is from the energy center
to the plexus,

00:16:03.680 --> 00:16:09.840
and from the plexus, it goes
through the nerves into the organs.

00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:18.240
That is how the energy center - the chakra -
governs the functioning

00:16:18.240 --> 00:16:22.160
of the human body
in the autonomic nervous system.

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:24.960
That’s essentially the schema.

00:16:24.960 --> 00:16:28.400
So, you have the energy center
that has the energy

00:16:28.400 --> 00:16:32.240
that, quote-unquote, controls—
I have to use hand quotes here—

00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:37.280
because there is no real neurotransmitter-y
system, as we discussed last time.

00:16:37.280 --> 00:16:39.760
There is no acetylcholine,
there is no adrenaline,

00:16:39.760 --> 00:16:43.520
there is no dopamine 
or serotonin that does it.

00:16:43.520 --> 00:16:50.080
But through ways that we have not yet elucidated,
but you can feel it through your awareness

00:16:50.080 --> 00:16:54.800
once you practice this form of meditation,
that the energy flows

00:16:54.800 --> 00:17:01.120
from the energy center to the plexus,
from the plexus to the organ,

00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:09.200
and that is how the chakra, plexus, organ system
functions to maintain, once again,

00:17:09.200 --> 00:17:13.600
the balance in the body,
the internal ecosystem of the body.

00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:17.120
That is how the nadis 
and the chakras come together.

00:17:17.120 --> 00:17:20.480
It is very important to remember,
as we go on our journey

00:17:20.480 --> 00:17:28.240
and we discuss this in future episodes,
that we should avoid the trap

00:17:28.240 --> 00:17:34.560
that modern medicine has fallen into,
which is to look at individual components

00:17:34.560 --> 00:17:37.680
and then try to make a sense of the whole.

00:17:37.680 --> 00:17:42.480
To understand the human spiritual system
or the subtle system, one needs to take, in fact,

00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:45.760
the directly opposite approach,
which is a holistic approach,

00:17:45.760 --> 00:17:51.760
to start from understanding
that the system functions in an integrated fashion,

00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:53.360
and to try to break it down

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:57.040
into its components 
is a reductive approach.

00:17:57.040 --> 00:18:00.320
But, at the same time, it does help
to understand a little bit,

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:02.880
but that is how it functions.

00:18:02.880 --> 00:18:07.680
So, even if one chakra controls,
maybe in theory, one plexus,

00:18:07.680 --> 00:18:12.400
in reality, it probably controls
many, many more plexuses

00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:17.440
and functions in ways that are very complex,
that human understanding still hasn't

00:18:17.440 --> 00:18:18.640
been able to pattern.

