00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:41.760
which looks at the body
as a composition of five elements:

00:25:41.760 --> 00:25:45.440
earth, fire, water, ether, and air.

00:25:45.440 --> 00:25:49.760
So, it is through the tridosha theory—
this tripartite theory—

00:25:49.760 --> 00:25:58.320
that we try to understand the relationship
between the subtle system and the gross system,

00:25:58.320 --> 00:26:05.120
and Ayurveda tries to use these elements
to bring the body to a state of balance.

00:26:05.120 --> 00:26:08.560
But that's as far as medical systems go.

00:26:08.560 --> 00:26:11.600
There are other systems of medicine;
the Chinese system tries to balance

00:26:11.600 --> 00:26:13.440
the yin and yang part of it.

00:26:13.440 --> 00:26:18.160
So, medicine historically has had
an understanding of it,

00:26:18.160 --> 00:26:22.560
but not to the extent
that Sahaj can provide.

