The pelvic plexus is formed by nerves
that come out of the sacrum bone

00:31:35.840 --> 00:31:40.000
and as well as the last parts
of the lumbar vertebra.

00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:46.160
They come together, they exist on both sides,
and the pelvic plexus innervates

00:31:46.160 --> 00:31:50.400
the excretory organs
as well as the reproductive organs

00:31:50.400 --> 00:31:54.240
in the human body,
in males as well as females,

00:31:54.240 --> 00:31:58.400
as shown in the animation.

00:31:58.400 --> 00:32:03.040
For example, the uterus
or the urinary bladder,

00:32:03.040 --> 00:32:08.320
the excretory organs, those are the organs
that are controlled —

00:32:08.320 --> 00:32:13.200
again, the word 'control' is used
in a spiritual sense, not just in a physical sense —

00:32:13.200 --> 00:32:14.720
by the pelvic plexus.

00:32:14.720 --> 00:32:19.200
The pelvic plexus—there are two of them
on either side of the vertebral column

00:32:19.200 --> 00:32:24.400
at the lower part of the body (the lower pelvis).
That's why it's called the pelvic plexus,

00:32:24.400 --> 00:32:27.520
and that's how they control these organs.

00:32:27.520 --> 00:32:33.440
But the power that controls the plexuses
is represented by the Muladhara chakra.

